And for the record, I find my debufs are quite useful when our group is fighting tough mobs. Sometimes it takes several casts to get them to stick, but often they stick right away. When they do, and the fight is drawn out, it makes a lot of difference.<P>Just the other day I joined a guild group (replacing another member who was leaving, so group size didn't change), and we were single pulling deep purples. The tanks told me immediately that they had an easier time hitting these mobs, and that they weren't taking as much damage as before I came.<P>I've partnered with paladins before. With my debufs, the pally's heal chant kept him almost full health the whole time. He thanked me for coming to help.<P>Just sharing my experience.<P>--------------------<P>Naeen<BR>Sorceror of 33 seasons<BR>Morgan Le Fay
