<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Debuffs have a use. They are the best way to conserver pet health when soloing orange mobs. I pull with cripple, debuff str/con, str, dex, dex/qui and then send the pet in.<P>Saving power as a Sorcerer is not an issue when solo.  Saving you pets hp is the biggest challenge.<P>In a small group, 2 or 3, debuffs can really help you take reds and purples faster, but if the group has more than 4 people then debuffs start to head into the useless category.  <P>It is a little funny when you think about it.  Mythic gave us debuffs to make us group friendly, but they are actually most usefull to us solo. Same with the bladeturn line, I get more use from that when in small pve groups or solo than I do in rvr (archers still kill me when they want).<P>Battik
